WEBVTT

00:05:57.665 --> 00:06:00.582
you know, Franklin Roosevelt
was never shown in a wheelchair,

00:06:00.606 --> 00:06:03.052
John F. Kennedy's affairs were ignored.

00:06:03.076 --> 00:06:07.267
It was only with Watergate

00:06:07.291 --> 00:06:10.871
that journalists were able
to speak truth to power

00:06:10.895 --> 00:06:13.699
and affect social change
and brought down Nixon -- yes!

00:06:14.132 --> 00:06:18.847
And it's the movies like "The Post"
and "All the President's Men"

00:06:18.871 --> 00:06:22.133
that the glory in journalism
is often thought to be

00:06:22.157 --> 00:06:26.641
exposing the corruption and evil of power.

00:06:26.665 --> 00:06:28.990
And that's obviously a very good thing.

00:06:29.014 --> 00:06:31.375
But it changes the mission of journalism